Vascular congestion","Mucosal ulceration","Subserosal fibrosis"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe key histological features that distinguish chronic from acute cholecystitis include the type of inflammatory infiltrate and tissue remodeling changes.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubserosal fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a characteristic feature of chronic cholecystitis, representing tissue remodeling and scarring from prolonged inflammation. \u003Cstrong\u003EMucosal ulceration\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eneutrophilic infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Evascular congestion\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Emucosal oedema\u003C/strong\u003E are all features typically seen in acute cholecystitis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EIn chronic cholecystitis, the acute inflammatory changes are replaced by:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ELymphoplasmacytic infiltration\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EFibrosis of the gallbladder wall\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EThickening of the wall\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ERokitansky-Aschoff sinuses\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic cholecystitis shows fibrosis and lymphocytic infiltration of the gallbladder wall.","Acute cholecystitis is characterised by neutrophilic infiltration and mucosal ulceration.","The transition from acute to chronic cholecystitis involves replacement of acute inflammatory cells with chronic inflammatory cells and tissue remodeling."],"references":["Gallaher JR, Charles A. Acute Cholecystitis: A Review. JAMA. 2022 Mar 8;327(10):965-975. doi: 10.1001/jama.2022.2350. PMID: 35258527.","Jones MW, Gnanapandithan K, Panneerselvam D, Ferguson T. Chronic Cholecystitis. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29261986.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48800"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15430"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48800","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48800"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-20T14:06:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-20T14:06:34+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8121"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63349"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udca9","name":"Gastrointestinal","s